title: Bug 121170 - get column label from meta data object should return some user recognizable strings
OB: When calling IMetaData.getColumnLabel() before data extraction, it is returning an empty string instead of user recognizable labels. After data extraction, the method returns the correct labels.
EB: The method IMetaData.getColumnLabel() should return the same user recognizable labels before and after data extraction.
SR:
To reproduce the issue:
 1. Call IMetaData.getColumnLabel() before data extraction.
 2. Extract the data.
 3. Call IMetaData.getColumnLabel() again.
 4. Compare the results.
